<subSubSection id="A88F953FEFBD453A69548CB4DD603EF0" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" type="description">
<paragraph id="3624250DA1363F27C9B7FD2BF2E77F3B" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Diagnostic description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="68EB52E7EE6EE060F971E9E40B08BD05" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
Overall dark brown to black. Pronotal disc (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C813AFA796C1A2C88B7A4F23B0416C11" captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Costalampys klugii (Motschulsky) comb. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antenna, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Sternum IX, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543220" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">17F</figureCitation>
) either with paired orangish or pinkish vittae on anterior corners, or entirely orangish or pinkish, pronotal expansions sometimes with a fine testaceous outline surrounding the disc, otherwise dark brown to black. Elytron (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="CD12C3ADC47D516ADCA046C8A651CB5C" captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Costalampys klugii (Motschulsky) comb. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antenna, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Sternum IX, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543220" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">17A, D</figureCitation>
) dark brown to black. Legs dark brown to black, except for trochanters and femora, which are lighter ventrally. Sternum VIII (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="0A63ADBF73CA80E4F99349E5F3AAFBEF" captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Costalampys klugii (Motschulsky) comb. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antenna, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Sternum IX, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543220" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">17G</figureCitation>
) entirely dark brown, without lateral vitreous spots. Pygidium (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="37E688F0B61F9F9FD0B227F0A1B90337" captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Costalampys klugii (Motschulsky) comb. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antenna, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Sternum IX, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543220" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">17H</figureCitation>
) entirely dark brown.
</paragraph>
<caption id="4C754EBD9E3192613E0204872FFEBD9B" doi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543220" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" start="Figure 17" startId="F17">
