<paragraph id="D6132BB141B8131E445475A161E0916F" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
Pronotum (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="38D1EAEE561496D8E903E094DF951AF8" captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Costalampys klugii (Motschulsky) comb. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antenna, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Sternum IX, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543220" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">17F</figureCitation>
) with anterior margin slightly acuminate, sides rounded, divergent posteriorly. Sternum VI (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="13232D37F296FB0707676D7FF1992AA9" captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Costalampys klugii (Motschulsky) comb. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antenna, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Sternum IX, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543220" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">17B</figureCitation>
) without lanterns. 
<emphasis id="E0D6F4A788C951F60495842F49B6412C" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Male.</emphasis>
Total length = 10.3-10.9 mm (aver. 10.6 mm); Pronotal length = 2.0-2.2 mm (aver. 2.1 mm); Pronotal width = 3.2-3.3 mm (aver. 3.25 mm); Elytral length = 8.4-8.6 mm (aver. 8.5 mm); Elytral width = 2.0-2.1 mm (aver. 2.05 mm). Antennomere III (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="3EC15FF1A282A1054FA58B1124E1FFE3" captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Costalampys klugii (Motschulsky) comb. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antenna, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Sternum IX, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543220" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">17E</figureCitation>
) with lamella 1.5-2
<normalizedToken id="C98BD7456B54BC8EDF5E566DFFD4944A" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than core antennomere. Sternum VIII (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="09B2679068F50BA8FA8362E012841CF5" captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Costalampys klugii (Motschulsky) comb. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antenna, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Sternum IX, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543220" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">17G</figureCitation>
) with posterior margin bisinuose. Pygidium (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="1D4F2F0284739669061076D8CB3B57E1" captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Costalampys klugii (Motschulsky) comb. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antenna, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Sternum IX, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543220" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">17H</figureCitation>
) with sides rounded, posterior corners weakly developed, posterior margin truncate. Syntergite (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F8494E4BEB4A2EDC3D4171638048C03A" captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Costalampys klugii (Motschulsky) comb. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antenna, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Sternum IX, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543220" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">17I, J</figureCitation>
) with anterior margin mildly curved. Phallus (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F9BDE979EE3198AF8D22EA7509998742" captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Costalampys klugii (Motschulsky) comb. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antenna, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Sternum IX, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543220" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">17K-M</figureCitation>
) with dorsal plate almost straight in lateral view, with sides straight and acuminate at apical half. Paramere apex curved ventrally, ventral projection (lateral view) weakly developed, rounded. 
<emphasis id="E1BCC4E75131FB35E1CB12289C35247D" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Female</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="BD33C669880F0E2BB2C56F333F51CC75" captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Costalampys klugii (Motschulsky) comb. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antenna, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Sternum IX, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543220" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">17C, D</figureCitation>
). Total length = 10.3 mm; Pronotal length = 2.2 mm; Pronotal width = 3.0 mm; Elytral length = 8 mm; Elytral width = 2.0 mm. Antennomeres III-X (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6BC67CBC3D854F8A936A464D0A7D184B" captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Costalampys klugii (Motschulsky) comb. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antenna, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Sternum IX, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543220" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">17C, D</figureCitation>
) with apical corners slightly projected and pointed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7C5557C924EC3FA34E2B24B0539443D5" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="332F35A1B6175BE04BE5552D576D9751" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2B36C93DDB7B73E04A91BC9894706901" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
<taxonomicName id="68EA879A39C652351FDC18729050DA6A" authorityName="da Silveira &amp; Roza &amp; Vaz &amp; Mermudes" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="da Silveira &amp; Roza &amp; Vaz &amp; Mermudes" baseAuthorityYear="2021" family="Lampyridae" genus="Lychnuris" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lychnuris klugii" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="klugii">
<emphasis id="29752971CAF7FFD2B111B7820290A230" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Lychnuris klugii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by 
<bibRefCitation id="EBC058C9B90B50A9743554482E93EB8A" author="Motschulsky, V" journalOrPublisher="Etudes Entomologiques" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" refId="B38" refString="Motschulsky, V, 1853. Lampyrides (Continuation). Etudes Entomologiques 2: 1.32." title="Lampyrides (Continuation). Etudes Entomologiques 2: 1.32." year="1853">Motschulsky (1853</bibRefCitation>
: 4), who wrongly attributed the species authorship to Dejean. Indeed, 
<bibRefCitation id="96FDD7B96F8A34F4112B5AB5AF331660" author="Dejean, PFMA" journalOrPublisher="Mequignon-Marvis, Paris" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" refId="B12" refString="Dejean, PFMA, 1833. Catalogue des Coleopteres de la collection de M. le Comte Dejean. Mequignon-Marvis, Paris" title="Catalogue des Coleopteres de la collection de M. le Comte Dejean." year="1833">Dejean (1833)</bibRefCitation>
cited 
<taxonomicName id="23992CEFAB5E66BBF08CA0C47D9F2E8C" authorityName="da Silveira &amp; Roza &amp; Vaz &amp; Mermudes" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="da Silveira &amp; Roza &amp; Vaz &amp; Mermudes" baseAuthorityYear="2021" family="Lampyridae" genus="Lychnuris" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lychnuris klugii" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="klugii">
<emphasis id="64D2F6730BC10EE023AD3171AB023A34" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Lychnuris klugii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in his second catalog, but without a description, making it therefore a 
<emphasis id="9ECD3DAEE4024DD0048EB66703F446FD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">nomen nudum</emphasis>
(cf. 
<bibRefCitation id="7DAE10FC563D8B1D6AB02BA52AAB557E" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.282.4401" author="Bousquet, Y" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" pagination="1 - 219" refId="B6" refString="Bousquet, Y, Bouchard, P, 2013. The genera in the second catalogue (1833-1836) of Dejean's Coleoptera collection. ZooKeys 282: 1 - 219, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.282.4401" title="The genera in the second catalogue (1833 - 1836) of Dejean's Coleoptera collection." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.282.4401" volume="282" year="2013">Bousquet and Bouchard 2013</bibRefCitation>
). The correct authorship of the species belongs to 
<bibRefCitation id="0EA50FF790E201A39D2AF97ED2F18F1A" author="Motschulsky, V" journalOrPublisher="Etudes Entomologiques" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" refId="B38" refString="Motschulsky, V, 1853. Lampyrides (Continuation). Etudes Entomologiques 2: 1.32." title="Lampyrides (Continuation). Etudes Entomologiques 2: 1.32." year="1853">Motschulsky (1853)</bibRefCitation>
, who in first provided a description for 
<taxonomicName id="ED4AB1C7250D9764AA6AD0FA5AFE6A17" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Lychnacris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lychnacris klugii" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="klugii">
<emphasis id="EE1ECE9E3B98D9C34B9D03F6713B3BF7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Lychnacris klugii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="55C0FF10978440C4D13096A502334180" author="Motschulsky, V" journalOrPublisher="Etudes Entomologiques" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" refId="B38" refString="Motschulsky, V, 1853. Lampyrides (Continuation). Etudes Entomologiques 2: 1.32." title="Lampyrides (Continuation). Etudes Entomologiques 2: 1.32." year="1853">Motschulsky (1853)</bibRefCitation>
lists the species for Southern Brazil, without further details.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EE6198CF667D22D4EEB7857C781BEF39" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
<normalizedToken id="5A0A3A035FD32BCEC8EE3CE588B9B985" originalValue="McDermott’s">McDermott's</normalizedToken>
catalog (1966) cites Motschulsky, 1853: 28 as a first mention of 
<taxonomicName id="76AFE30D43B97E6B3880ABC47FFAD5C3" authorityName="da Silveira &amp; Roza &amp; Vaz &amp; Mermudes" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="da Silveira &amp; Roza &amp; Vaz &amp; Mermudes" baseAuthorityYear="2021" family="Lampyridae" genus="Lychnuris" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lychnuris klugii" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="klugii">
<emphasis id="09DD0E12B40977BB3878A4F787848CD5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Lychnuris klugii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but this is inaccurate in two ways. On one side, the first citation of 
<taxonomicName id="F23FB0ACFFDA3A4A224D55E429171374" authorityName="da Silveira &amp; Roza &amp; Vaz &amp; Mermudes" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="da Silveira &amp; Roza &amp; Vaz &amp; Mermudes" baseAuthorityYear="2021" family="Lampyridae" genus="Lychnuris" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lychnuris klugii" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="klugii">
<emphasis id="AF2F83D9BD44ADBB5261D791797E0700" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Lychnuris klugii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was indeed on a &quot;page 28&quot;, but in 1852, not 1853. However, we interpret that in 
<bibRefCitation id="CF2A3447223C92B562D5D610CC1E7F41" author="Motschulsky, V" journalOrPublisher="Etudes Entomologiques" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" pagination="25 - 58" refId="B37" refString="Motschulsky, V, 1852. Lampyrides. Etudes Entomologiques 1: 25 - 58" title="Lampyrides." volume="1" year="1852">Motschulsky 1852</bibRefCitation>
: 28, 
<taxonomicName id="312A4EAACCE99E42692F0622243E0E94" genus="L." lsidName="L. klugii" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="klugii">
<emphasis id="E2BA6FB53BA8C7D910B0A2A20FBD1A25" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">L. klugii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a 
<emphasis id="7D8F89A6460D8CB24E44BA8628384B6A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">nomen nudum</emphasis>
, as the synopsis given regards the genus 
<taxonomicName id="5604FBFC217ECD2C0CA189FB1DFFEE69" family="Lampyridae" genus="Lychnuris" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lychnuris" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B7BB0F09B31A8341DD29C3A473D35004" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Lychnuris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Dejean, 1833 (valid 
<emphasis id="967E93B9107078E73CB3AE98D43607F8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">fide</emphasis>
Bousquet &amp; Bouchard, 2013), not the species. The correct reference of the species description, as listed above, is Motschulsky, 1853: 4.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4E5FC93BF35750828573050E28B954BB" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
<bibRefCitation id="F284E683BB1EDD1C6F87DDCD7501E78C" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-2311.1880.tb02016.x" author="Gorham, HS" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" pagination="1 - 36" refId="B21" refString="Gorham, HS, 1880. I. Materials for a revision of the Lampyridae. Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London 28: 1 - 36, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-2311.1880.tb02016.x" title="I. Materials for a revision of the Lampyridae." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-2311.1880.tb02016.x" volume="28" year="1880">Gorham (1880)</bibRefCitation>
transferred 
<taxonomicName id="425CE773844BA2292192C09EBF7A9378" authorityName="Motschoulsky" authorityYear="1853" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Lychnacris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lychnacris" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="57EADB004FBE323152F445E7AE2CAE9B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Lychnacris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="8A9A052D2EE7166B5C45DC0EB34F1F97" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Lucidota" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lucidota" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DD983E81789CD27A707E24EE482FCD8A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Lucidota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Laporte, 1833. Since then, it was transferred to 
<taxonomicName id="DD8C73070E2B30C404D9019EF9696CFE" family="Lampyridae" genus="Lychnuris" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lychnuris" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="AB27F414320C51DEB3F401BB571BC2B2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Lychnuris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="FB250E26BF09ECB554EDEDB3E8732652" author="Olivier, E" journalOrPublisher="Revue scientifique du Bourbonnais et du centre de la France" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" pagination="39 - 58" refId="B46" refString="Olivier, E, 1911. Revision des Lampyrides. Revue scientifique du Bourbonnais et du centre de la France 24: 39 - 58" title="Revision des Lampyrides." volume="24" year="1911">Olivier (1911)</bibRefCitation>
, and back to 
<taxonomicName id="4008A0D5AC5D23E54B6FC54B90C2BBC7" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Lucidota" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lucidota" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4E630B1039B688D6CF459EABC2BED139" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Lucidota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="ADEE6D28E1537FFD342E100B40579BC2" author="McDermott, FA" editor="Steel, WO" journalOrPublisher="Pars 9 (editio secunda). W. Junk, S'Gravenhage" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" pagination="1 - 149" refId="B34" refString="McDermott, FA, 1966. Lampyridae. In: Steel, WO, Ed., , Coleopterorum Catalogus Supplementa. Pars 9 (editio secunda). W. Junk, S'Gravenhage: 1 - 149" title="Lampyridae." volumeTitle=", Coleopterorum Catalogus Supplementa." year="1966">McDermott (1966)</bibRefCitation>
. After our phylogenetic analysis (see section 3.2), we transfer 
<taxonomicName id="8C4DC477B13010D9E0FC6A492CAD8A5B" authorityName="da Silveira &amp; Roza &amp; Vaz &amp; Mermudes" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="da Silveira &amp; Roza &amp; Vaz &amp; Mermudes" baseAuthorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Lucidota" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lucidota klugii" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="klugii">
<emphasis id="FAE7D540AE754B9BF45D86D25EE614A9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Lucidota klugii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Motschulsky, 1853) to 
<taxonomicName id="7E7A015E4A28C35B0D81F2937338A209" authority="Silveira, Roza, Vaz &amp; Mermudes, 2021-14" authorityName="Silveira, Roza, Vaz &amp; Mermudes, 2021-14" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Costalampys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Costalampys" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="723E88F9D53C454C07805748FDBD563D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Costalampys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="5BA29C0EC577EDEB3A661490BBD3C1DA" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">gen. nov.</emphasis>
, therefore 
<taxonomicName id="CBCD7DFB8759B88C4AABAB7B8433D048" authority="Silveira, Roza, Vaz &amp; Mermudes, 2021-14" authorityName="Motschulsky" authorityYear="1853" baseAuthorityName="da Silveira &amp; Roza &amp; Vaz &amp; Mermudes" baseAuthorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Costalampys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Costalampys klugii" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="klugii">
<emphasis id="6C2A3F958F32C208A5A6671CEB92BF4E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Costalampys klugii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Motschulsky, 1853) 
<emphasis id="85A6854575893361C1A53ACAB5C7FA59" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">comb. nov.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2FE354D75F7F069DA331D66EEC6C5F00" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
<taxonomicName id="75A3DBC89B071DC22275FABA202FE429" authority="Silveira, Roza, Vaz &amp; Mermudes, 2021-14" authorityName="Motschulsky" authorityYear="1853" baseAuthorityName="da Silveira &amp; Roza &amp; Vaz &amp; Mermudes" baseAuthorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Costalampys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Costalampys klugii" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="klugii">
<emphasis id="B916DFD7A29AD97B7569635476494825" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Costalampys klugii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Motschulsky, 1853 
<emphasis id="8D3382DF44F1A72C562929F36495BD78" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">comb. nov.</emphasis>
is very unique among other 
<taxonomicName id="BE57BF0E223E7ACEA9923ABC2AF97754" authority="Silveira, Roza, Vaz &amp; Mermudes, 2021-14" authorityName="Silveira, Roza, Vaz &amp; Mermudes, 2021-14" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Costalampys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Costalampys" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CE39C7C95D8E9B97CEEBA7D97C3AA554" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Costalampys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. in lacking an elongate elytral pale-yellow spot. The paired pink vittae usually seen in the pronotum is often found as well in 
<taxonomicName id="B3BE5B877FCC0BEF59A0EC9214C4CE99" genus="C." lsidName="C. tricolor" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="tricolor">
<emphasis id="5A1B213AA7C6828D09784961B0D2EA28" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">C. tricolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Gorham, 1880) 
<emphasis id="C42BEE1E9FF0AEA2AE040DB29E508795" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">comb. nov.</emphasis>
, from which 
<taxonomicName id="7DD5B65995C97F76E50FA6E6C5059291" genus="C." lsidName="C. klugii" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="klugii">
<emphasis id="F97CF0BE9A3EBEC4F005C287409F9D60" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">C. klugii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Motschulsky, 1853 
<emphasis id="04241E1C8CB7CE7EE330F895DE5695AD" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">comb. nov.</emphasis>
can be distinguished by the lack of an elongate, elytral pale-yellow stripe, and lack of lanterns on sternum VI (both traits present in 
<taxonomicName id="476E153C2C3B75660C72F111A30B8F6E" genus="C." lsidName="C. tricolor" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="tricolor">
<emphasis id="47029DE5F69C386D72F3D0E530077BD4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">C. tricolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Gorham, 1880) 
<emphasis id="21AAD75327A91EA6A80ECC8F616EEE54" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">comb. nov.</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
